==English==

===Etymology===
First attested [[w:1853|1853]] in a Texas context, possibly from the notion of proceeding by leaps or because the kangaroo's appearance defies nature. 

===Noun===
'''[[kangaroo]] [[court]]''' {{wikipedia}}

# a [[fraudulent]] or [[unjust]] trial where the decision has essentially been made in advance, usually for the purpose of providing a conviction.

